article.headline: Illinois State 87, Bellarmine 53
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Trey Guidry scored 20 points and four other teammates also scored in the double digits as Illinois State beat Bellarmine 87-53 Tuesday night. Chris Burras added 17 points for the Redbirds (2-2). Vince Greene also chipped in 14 points, while Marcus Arnold scored 12 points and Neil Plank finished with 10. Illinois State led 34-11 with 5:35 remaining in the first after Guidry nailed a 3-pointer to cap a 9-0 run. The Redbirds went on to take a 40-23 lead at the half. Bellarmine (1-5) edged Illinois State in rebounding 43-40 but were held to just 32 percent shooting, compared to 49 percent for the Redbirds. The Knights were led by Victor Pierson, who scored 18 points and Justin Cornell, who had 10. Troy Brown pulled down a game-high 14 rebounds for Bellarmine.
